15/08/2010
TOKYO, Japan -- A Montenegrin member of the notorious Pink Panthers crime gang suspected of an armed robbery in a Tokyo jewellery shop three years ago was extradited from Spain to Japan on Saturday (August 14th). Rifat Hadziahmetovic, 42, arrived in Tokyo and was taken to police headquarters in the expensive Ginza quarter, where the shop he allegedly robbed is located. He was serving a sentence for another crime in Spain. The Pink Panthers, believed to be comprised of mostly Balkan members, are suspected of stealing jewels worth more than 250m euros from various stores worldwide. (CNN, BBC, UPI, Euronews- 14/08/10)
